# 1. Title
**Deep Learning for Credit Default Prediction: Mitigating Non-Performing Asset (NPA) Risks in Indian Banking Using Artificial Neural Networks**

---

# 2. Overview of the Presentation
This comprehensive report details the end-to-end development of an advanced Deep Learning predictive system designed to address one of the most critical macroeconomic vulnerabilities in emerging markets: the proliferation of Non-Performing Assets (NPAs). Operating specifically within the context of the Indian banking sector, this study moves beyond generic linear machine learning techniques (such as Logistic Regression or isolated Decision Trees). Instead, it engineers an Artificial Neural Network (ANN) utilizing the PyTorch framework. 

This model actively synthesizes two massive streams of financial data—proprietary internal bank behavior and universal external credit bureau (CIBIL) histories—to forecast the precise Probability of Default (PD). By predicting four granular risk profiles (`P1` to `P4`) rather than relying on binary classification, this project provides a significantly higher resolution of customer reliability. Achieving over 92% validation accuracy on previously unseen customer applications, the study translates highly technical mathematical metrics into a suite of actionable, profit-driving managerial strategies, encompassing dynamic risk-based interest pricing, automated hyper-fast underwriting, and strategic capital allocation required by regulatory bodies like the Reserve Bank of India (RBI).

